/* ===== Legal ===== */
"legal.terms.title"              = "Terms of Service";
"legal.privacy.title"            = "Privacy Policy";
"legal.terms.body"               = "By using MadFrog VPN you agree to the following terms.\n\n1. Service\nMadFrog VPN provides encrypted VPN tunneling for personal, non-commercial use.\n\n2. Acceptable use\nYou may not use the service for illegal activity, abuse of third-party services, port scanning, spam, or any action that breaches the laws of your jurisdiction.\n\n3. Subscriptions\nPaid plans are sold through the Apple App Store and are non-recurring (one-time purchases for a fixed duration). Refunds are handled by Apple.\n\n4. Liability\nThe service is provided \"as is\" without warranty. We are not liable for interruptions, blocked traffic, or loss of data.\n\n5. Termination\nWe may suspend accounts that violate these terms. You can delete your account at any time from Settings → Account.\n\nLast updated: April 2026.";
"legal.privacy.body"             = "MadFrog VPN follows a strict no-logs policy for your VPN traffic.\n\n1. We never log your VPN activity\nWe do not record the content of your traffic, the sites or services you connect to, your DNS queries, or your browsing history. Your VPN traffic stays private.\n\n2. What we store to run the service\n• Your anonymous account identifier, subscription status, and VPN credentials.\n• Connection & device context: when the app contacts our servers we record the source IP address, an approximate country derived from it, device model, OS and app version, language, time zone, and App Store region. Used for security, fraud prevention, and diagnostics — this is your app's connection to our API, never the content or destinations of your VPN traffic.\n• Basic in-app events (such as launch and connect) to keep the service reliable.\n\n3. Support chat\nIf you contact support in the app, we store your messages, any files you attach, and — only if you use the diagnostics button — a snapshot of your app and device state and a connection log. Used solely to help you; kept up to 90 days after the conversation, then deleted.\n\n4. Notifications\nIf you allow notifications, we store an Apple push token to notify you about support replies and important updates.\n\n5. Payments\nPayments go through the App Store. We never see your card data — Apple sends only a transaction id and a signed receipt, which we verify.\n\n6. Sign in with Apple\nWe receive a hashed identifier; your real email only if you choose to share it.\n\n7. Account deletion\nDelete your account anytime from Settings → Account. Deletion is immediate and permanent.\n\nFull policy: madfrog.online/app/privacy\nLast updated: June 2026.";

